    "body": "Suspected transaction which is not handled correctly: https://etherscan.io/tx/0x955d8ce92ff82a7e21bdde0e35b1e7c9fcf74a7fb6b23fcf9a66ec08cc122f60\r\n\r\nNext step is to produce the execution trace of this transaction by uncommenting the code in `state_processor.go` (in `ApplyTransaction` function), and running the code through the error. The trace would be in the file `structlogs.txt`\r\n\r\nNext, we will extract the correct trace using `debug_traceTransaction` RPC call and compare. Here is how to request the correct trace:\r\n````\r\ncurl -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\", \"method\":\"debug_traceTransaction\", \"params\":[\"0x955d8ce92ff82a7e21bdde0e35b1e7c9fcf74a7fb6b23fcf9a66ec08cc122f60\"],\"id\":0}'\r\n````\r\nAppend the URL to this command",
